---

Toast @Belgian Waffle{2%unit} until golden. Drop @honey{4%teaspoon}(in packet) in a small #bowl{} of warm water to soften. Roughly chop @cashews{1/2%ounce}.

Heat a medium dry pan over medium-high heat. Add cashews and @shredded coconut{1/4%cup}; cook, stirring frequently, until lightly browned and fragrant, ~{2-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}.

> Keep a close eye on pan to avoid burning.

Once waffles are toasted, cut into 1/4-inch pieces.

In a second small bowl, whisk together @yogurt{3/4%cup}, @crème fraîche{4%tablespoon}, honey, and a pinch of @salt{} until well combined.

If using #jars{}, divide half the honey yogurt between jars. Top with half the @berry compote{3%ounce}, half the toasted cashews and coconut, and half the waffle pieces. Repeat to make a second layer. If using #bowls{}, divide honey yogurt between bowls. Top with berry compote and toasted cashews and coconut. Place waffle pieces in the center. Serve.